update texts set name="Limit Reverse", desc="Target 1 monster with 1000 or less ATK in your Graveyard; Special Summon it in Attack Position. If the target is changed to Defense Position, destroy it and this card. When this card leaves the field, destroy the target. When the target is destroyed, destroy this card." where id=27551
;update texts set name="The 13th Grave", desc="A zombie that suddenly appeared from plot #13 - an empty grave." where id=32864
;update texts set name="D/D Savant Thomas", desc="Pendulum Effect
During your Main Phase: You can add 1 face-up ""D/D"" Pendulum Monster from your Extra Deck to your hand. You can only use this effect of ""D/D Savant Thomas"" once per turn.

Monster Effect
You can target 1 ""D/D"" card in your Pendulum Zone; destroy that card, and if you do, Special Summon 1 Level 8 ""D/D/D"" monster from your Deck in Defense Position, but for the rest of this turn, its effects (if any) are negated, and any battle damage your opponent takes becomes halved. You can only use this effect of ""D/D Savant Thomas"" once per turn." where id=41546
;update texts set name="Gem-Enhancement", desc="Tribute 1 ""Gem-Knight"" monster, then target 1 ""Gem-Knight"" monster in your Graveyard; Special Summon that target from the Graveyard." where id=41777
;update texts set name="Magician's Circle", desc="When a Spellcaster-Type monster declares an attack: Each player Special Summons 1 Spellcaster-Type monster with 2000 or less ATK from their Deck in Attack Position." where id=50755
;update texts set name="Castle of Dark Illusions", desc="FLIP: All Zombie-Type monsters gain 200 ATK and DEF. During each of your next 4 Standby Phases, each of those Zombie-Type monsters gains 200 more ATK and DEF. These effects last as long as this card is face-up on the field." where id=62121
;update texts set name="Cipher Spectrum", desc="If a ""Cipher"" Xyz Monster(s) you control that has Xyz Material is destroyed by battle or an opponent's card effect and sent to your Graveyard: Target 1 of those monsters; Special Summon it, and if you do, Special Summon 1 Xyz Monster from your Extra Deck with the same name as that Xyz Monster." where id=98905;